article.description: Stu Douglass scored 16 of his 19 points in the second half as Michigan rallied to beat Harvard 65-62 Saturday. The game marked Harvard coach Tommy Amaker's return to Michigan, where he was in charge from 2001-07.
article.headline: Stu Douglass rallies Michigan past Harvard
article.linkText: Harvard loses in Amaker's return to Michigan
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. -- Stu Douglass scored 16 of his 19 points in the second half as Michigan rallied to beat Harvard 65-62 Saturday. The game marked Harvard coach Tommy Amaker's return to Michigan, where he was in charge from 2001-07. Zack Novak finished with 12 points and 11 rebounds for the Wolverines (5-2) while Darius Morris added 13 points. Keith Wright had 18 points and 12 rebounds for the Crimson (5-2). Harvard led by seven at halftime, and by as many as 12 early in the second half, but Michigan got back into the game behind three 3-pointers from Douglass. Novak scored twice to put Michigan up 58-52 with 2 minutes left, and after a Harvard basket, Douglass hit another 3-pointer. Morris later missed the front end of a 1-and-1 with 26 seconds left, and Brandyn Curry's layup got the Crimson within 62-59 but they couldn't pull any closer.
